The largest theatre in the city is the 2,300 capacity [[Mayflower Theatre]] (formerly known as the Gaumont), which, as the largest theatre in [[Southern England]] outside London, has hosted West End shows such as ''[[Les Misérables (musical)|Les Misérables]]'', ''[[The Rocky Horror Show]]'' and ''[[Chitty Chitty Bang Bang (musical)|Chitty Chitty Bang Bang]]'', as well as regular visits from [[Welsh National Opera]] and [[English National Ballet]]. There is also the Nuffield Theatre<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.nuffieldtheatre.co.uk/| accessdate =19 October 2009| author=The Nuffield Theatre| title = The Nuffield Southampton
