|title = University of Southampton| location=London| work=The Guardian}}</ref> The university has a global reputation for research into engineering sciences,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.southampton.ac.uk/ses/|accessdate =19 October 2007|author=University of Southampton
|title = School of Engineering Sciences}}</ref> [[oceanography]], [[chemistry]], [[cancer|cancer sciences]], sound and vibration research,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.isvr.soton.ac.uk|date = 9 October 2008|accessdate =9 October 2008|title = University of Southampton, Institute of Sound and Vibration Research}}</ref> computer science and electronics, [[optoelectronics]] and textile conservation at the Textile Conservation Centre<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.textileconservationcentre.soton.ac.uk/
|date = 9 October 2008|accessdate =9 October 2008|title = The Textile Conservation Centre, University of Southampton
}}</ref> (which is due to close in October 2009.) It is also home to the [[National Oceanography Centre, Southampton]] (NOCS), the focus of [[Natural Environment Research Council]]-funded [[marine (ocean)|marine]] research.

Southampton Solent University has 17,000<ref>{{cite news|url = http://education.guardian.co.uk/higher/universityguide/profile/story/0,,491283,00.html|date = 1 May 2007|accessdate =28 July 2007|author=Guardian Unlimited|title = Southampton Solent University
